  "Allegations" : "OCTOBER 1999, CUSTOMER WAS PRESENTED WITH A PLAN GIVING HER 3 ALTERNATIVES FOR HER INVESTMENT CHOICES. ALL THREE  CHOICED UTILIZED SOME FORM OF RISK MANAGEMENT TO ATTEMPT TO PROTECT HER FUNDS IN THE EVENT OF A DECLINING MARKET. SHE REVIEWED, SIGNED AND ACCEPTED THE PLAN AND SELECTED THE AMERICAN SKANDIA ASL ANNUITY USING RTE ASSET MANAGEMENT. THIS ANNUITY HAS NO SURRENDER CHARGES AND PAID HER A BONUS OF 1% TO START. SHE ALSO ACKNOWLEDGED RECEIVING THE PROSPECTUS,CONTRACT APPLICATION, INVESTMENT ACKNOWLEDGEMENT FORM AND INFO ON THIRD PARTY MANAGER, RTE. CUSTOMER ALSO ACKNOWLEDGED THAT SHE HAD DISCUSSED HER FINANCIAL BACKGROUND AND AS A RESULT, BELIEVED THAT THE CHOICE SHE SELECTED WOULD MEET HER NEEDS AND FINANCIAL OBJECTIVES. 2000/2001 PROVED TO BE DIFFICULT YEARS FOR THE FINANCIAL MARKETS, HER ACCOUNT DECLINED IN VALUE. I RECOMMENDED THAT SHE REPLACE THE THIRD PARTY MANAGER, RTE, WITH PORTFOLIO STRATEGIES INC ON NOVEMBER 2001. WE WERE THEN CONTACTED BY AN ANN HIROSHIGE WHO SAID SHE HAD FINANCIAL  POWER OF ATTORNEY ON BEHALF OF CUSTOMER AND SAID THAT HER ACCOUNT HAD GONE DOWN AND THAT SHE WAS GOING TO MOVE IT ELSEWHERE. WE WERE CONTACTED ON JANUARY 2002 BY THE BACK OFFICE AT LINSCO PRIVATE LEDGER TO HAVE THE ACCOUNT MOVED TO THEIR BROKERAGE ACCOUNT. I ADDRESSED A LETTER TO CUSTOMER RECOMMENDING THE FUNDS NOT BE TRANSFERRED OUT OF AMERICAN SKANDIA IN ORDER TO PROTECT THE VALUABLE DEATH BENEFIT THAT WAS ATTACHED, WHICH WOULD HAVE MADE UP FOR ANY LOSSES IN THE EVENT OF CUSTOMER'S DEATH WHERE ANN HIROSHIGE WAS BENEFICIARY OF ACCOUNT.  SHE THEN WROTE A LETTER DATED MAY 1,2002 STATING CUSTOMER'S ACCOUNT WAS MISREPRESENTED, MISMANAGED, UNSUITABLE AND INAPPROPRIATE.  JUNE 2002 MY BROKER DEALER DETERMINED THAT DAMAGES COULD BE MORE THAN $5000 BUT, AFTER REVIEW OF THIS COMPLAINT THE CLAIM WAS DENIED.",
